other_tests.findings: Absence of central retinal vasculature bilaterally.
Bilateral absence of peripheral retinal vessels and scarcity of vessels nasal to the disc; slow and segmental retinal and choroidal filling.
Near-absence of the optic chiasm; attenuated optic nerves; small optic tracts.
Small kidneys with diffusely increased echogenicity of the renal cortex and diminished cortico-medullary differentiation, consistent with renal dysplasia.

other_tests.procedure_name: Spectral Doppler ultrasonographic analysis of renal vasculature
other_tests.findings: High-resistance arterial flow in both main renal arteries with no blood flow detectable during diastole.
Dysplastic discs bilaterally with absent central retinal vessels on the right, marked attenuation of retinal vessels on the left.
Presence of a superonasal visual field defect.
Anomalous central retinal vasculature present at the level of the disc margin.
